Key Match Events: Germany's Denis Undav scored twice against Bosnia-Herzegovina
Bosnia's Ermedin Demirovic hit the woodwork in the 35th minute
Hungary's Roland Sallai put the host in the driver's seat in the 32nd minute
The Netherlands' Virgil van Dijk was sent off for a second yellow card
Denel Dumfries earned a point for the visitors with a header from Cody Gakpo's curled free kick in the 83rd minute
Pre-Game Insights: Germany coach Julian Nagelsmann expected Bosnia and Herzegovina to be good defensively
The Germans played with confidence, developed complex attacking moves and gave the impression of enjoying themselves
Post-Match Reflections: Germany coach Julian Nagelsmann said that Bosnia and Herzegovina stayed in the game due to Germany's many chances
Netherlands coach Ronald Koeman said that even with 10 men, they tried to put pressure forward and were relieved to still finish 1-1
Miscellaneous Highlights: Germany extended their unbeaten record in the Nations League to three matches
Germany opened a two-point lead over the Netherlands at the top of the A3 Group
Hungary held the Netherlands to a 1-1 draw, ending the Dutch's unbeaten run
Ukraine downs Georgia 1-0 in Group B1
Iceland erased a two-goal deficit to draw with Wales 2-2
Turkey defeated Montenegro 1-0 in the other Group B4 game
Estonia won against Azerbaijan 3-1 in League C
